This Should Be Done in Chronological Order
1.) Add Your .env Files

2.) Migrate Database
php artisan migrate

3.) Create Roles For You User Type in Your System
php artisan bouncer:seed

4.) Create Admin Account
php artisan db:seed

5.) Install Node Modules Dependancy
npm install

6.) Stripped Off Unnecessary Bloat on Your CSS
gulp uncss

7.) Remove Render Blocking Script
gulp critical

8.) Compress HTML in Cache
gulp compress

9.) Inline CSS For Email
gulp email

9.) Whitelist All Ports Needed by Your System
# Forge Server Network Firewall
- port 3001

10.) Enable Gzip Compress based on Your Site Content
- Edit nginx.conf , use HTML5 Boilerplate for nginx

11.) Secure Site With Let's Encrypt

12.) SSL Log Jam Fix
https://laravel-news.com/2016/01/optimizing-ssl-laravel-forge/
# Remove includeSubDomains , wont force ssl in subdomain
# This is Needed if you Using Email Services such as Mailgun
add_header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000";

12.) Enable Cloudflare and Configure DNS
# Remeber to Use Full Stric if your Using SSL

13.) Add to Your Daemon Socket Server to Start Every Restart
run node.js

14.) Listen to Jobs and Queues.
http://fideloper.com/ubuntu-beanstalkd-and-laravel4